  \begin{definition}[Field]
$(F,+,\times)$ is called a \emph{field} if
\begin{enumerate}
\item $(F,+, \times)$ is an Abelian Ring.
\item $(F \setminus 0, \times)$ is a (Abelian) group, where $0$ is the identity under $+$.
\end{enumerate}    
